                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>the <persName>Rev Dr Bondi</persName> We are much<lb/> pleased with the Rev Dr &amp;\n                think him<lb/> a perfect gentleman in his manner<lb/> as well as one well conversant\n                with<lb/> the Law; and I am truly grateful to<lb/> think we were saved from\n                falling<lb/> into the hands of <persName>Mr Phillips</persName>, whom<lb/> I\n                apprehend to be a man too mercenary<lb/> to have a proper view of a conversion<lb/>\n                One of the first questions he asked me<lb/> was “if the gentleman could afford<lb/>\n                to give as much as <persName>Mr Lawrence</persName>;” and<lb/> he endeavored to\n                impress on my mind<lb/> the necessity of keeping it secret; and<lb/> as much as\n                possible from the know<lb/>-ledge of the <persName>Revd I M Isaacs</persName>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">We regret that a succession of<lb/> disappointments &amp; troubles\n                should<lb/> have so long prevented us from<lb/> liquidating our indebtedness to</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3mp4w778/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
